headline: Assessing KLA (KLAC) Valuation After A Sharp Pullback And Strong Multi Year Gains
summary: Recent share performance and business profile KLA (KLAC) has recently seen a 3.6% one day decline and a 19.7% pullback over the past week, bringing the last close to US$1,307.22. That sits against a year total return of 73.7%. Over the past month the stock shows a 3.3% decline, while the past 3 months reflect an 8.4% total return and year to date performance stands at 2.6%. headline: KLA Declares Regular Cash Dividend
summary: The KLA Corporation (NASDAQ: KLAC) Board of Directors today declared a quarterly cash dividend of $1.90 per share on its common stock, payable on March 3, 2026 to KLA shareholders of record as of the close of business on Feb. 17, 2026.

headline: Flex's Q3 Earnings & Revenues Surpass Estimates, Increase Y/Y
summary: FLEX tops Q3 FY26 earnings and revenue estimates on strong AI-driven demand and raised full-year guidance, yet shares slid as investor concerns resurfaced.
